# BrainGrid Workflow — MicrohireAgentChat (PROJ-1)

Project is linked. No need to specify project IDs — they auto-resolve.

## New Feature

```bash
/specify "what you want to build"   # AI refines it into a requirement
/breakdown REQ-X                    # breaks it into tasks
git checkout -b feature/REQ-X-desc  # branch name auto-detects REQ-X
/build REQ-X                        # full plan with task prompts
```

## Bug Fix

```bash
/specify "Bug: <symptom> — <where it happens>"   # creates a tracked requirement
/breakdown REQ-X                                  # breaks into investigation + fix tasks
git checkout -b fix/REQ-X-short-desc
/build REQ-X                                      # get the fix plan
```

## Existing Project Change (refactor, tweak, config)

```bash
/specify "Change: <what needs changing and why>"
# Same flow as above — even small changes benefit from a tracked requirement
```

## Track Progress

```bash
braingrid task update TASK-X --status IN_PROGRESS   # before starting a task
braingrid task update TASK-X --status COMPLETED     # after finishing
braingrid requirement update REQ-X --status COMPLETED
```

## Useful Commands

```bash
braingrid requirement list                  # see all requirements
braingrid task list -r REQ-X               # see tasks for a requirement
braingrid requirement show                 # auto-detects from current branch
```

## Rules
- Always create a requirement before writing code — even for bugs
- Name branches `feature/REQ-X-*`, `fix/REQ-X-*`, or `chore/REQ-X-*`
- Mark tasks IN_PROGRESS before starting, COMPLETED immediately after
